Logmonrc

Type: object

root do

Do


Default action configuration.
All actions inherit these settings if they don't overwrite them.

  • LogActionConfig
  • Action String
root do anyOf LogActionConfig

LogActionConfig

Type: object

root do anyOf LogActionConfig subject

Subject

Type: string

Email subject template.
Default: '{brief}'

root do anyOf LogActionConfig body

Body

Type: string

Email body template.
Default: '{logfile}\n\n{entries_str}'

root do anyOf LogActionConfig host

Host

Type: string

Host to connect to for SMTP/IMAP/HTTP(S).
Default: 'localhost'

root do anyOf LogActionConfig port

Port

Type: integer

Port to connect to for SMTP/IMAP/HTTP(S) if not the standard port.

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root do anyOf LogActionConfig user

User

Type: string

Credentials for SMTP/IMAP, HTTP basic auth, or OAuth 2.0 password grant type.

root do anyOf LogActionConfig password

Password

Type: string

Credentials for SMTP/IMAP, HTTP basic auth, or OAuth 2.0 password grant type.

root do anyOf LogActionConfig secure
Type: enum (of null or string)

secure option for SMTP/IMAP.
Default: null

Must be one of:

  • null
  • "STARTTLS"
  • "SSL/TLS"

root do anyOf LogActionConfig logmails
Type: enum (of string)

Write messages to logmon's log instead of/in addition to performing the action.
Default: 'onerror'

Must be one of:

  • "always"
  • "never"
  • "onerror"
  • "instead"

Default: false

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command

Command

Type: array of string

Command to run if action is 'COMMAND'.

The template parameters are the same as with body plus the special syntax {...entries}, which makes the argument repeat as a separate argument for each entry. E.g. if there are the entries 'foo' and 'bar' the argument list ['command', '--entry={...entries}'] will expand to ['command', '--entry=foo', '--entry=bar']

No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command command items
Type: string

Example:

[
    "/path/to/command",
    "--sender",
    "{sender}",
    "--receivers",
    "{receivers}",
    "--",
    "{...entries}"
]

Working directory of spawned process.

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_env

Command Env

Type: object

Set the environment of the spawned process to this. Passing null as the value means to inherit that environment variable from the current environment. If this is unset the environment of the logmon process is inherited.

Each additional property must conform to the following schema

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_env additionalProperties

  • Option 1
  • Option 2
root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_env additionalProperties anyOf item 0
Type: string
root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_env additionalProperties anyOf item 1
Type: null

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_stdin

Command Stdin

Type: string

'file:/path/to/file', 'inherit:', 'null:', 'pipe:TEMPLATE'

The parameters to the TEMPLATE are the same as for body plus the special syntax {...entries} which causes the whole template to repeat for each entry.

Default: 'null:'

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_stdout

Command Stdout

Type: string

'file:/path/to/file', 'append:/path/to/file', 'inherit:', 'null:'

Default: 'null:'

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_stderr

Command Stderr

Type: string

'file:/path/to/file', 'append:/path/to/file', 'inherit:', 'null:', 'stdout:'

Default: 'null:'

root do anyOf LogActionConfig command_interactive

Command Interactive

Type: boolean

If true the process is long-running and log entries are passed by writing them to the stdin of the process instead of command line arguments.

Default: false

root do anyOf LogActionConfig action

Action


Action to perform.
This can also be a string in the form of one of these:

    {smtp,imap,http,https}[:[//][<user>[:<password>]@]<host>[:<port>][/<path>[?<query>]]]
    command[:<command> [<option>...]]
    {file,fifo}[:<path>]

Parameters defined here overwrite values passed via other options.

For SMTP and IMAP these query parameters are supported:

  • sender
  • receivers
  • secure

Default: 'SMTP'

  • ActionType
  • Action String
root do anyOf LogActionConfig action anyOf ActionType
Type: enum (of string)

Must be one of:

  • "SMTP"
  • "IMAP"
  • "HTTP"
  • "HTTPS"
  • "COMMAND"
  • "FILE"

Type: string

root do anyOf Action String

Action String

Type: string

root logfiles

Logfiles


The mapping keys or entries in the array of strings is the path of the log file.
You can read from a SystemD journal instead of a file by specifying a path in the form of:

systemd:{LOCAL_ONLY,RUNTIME_ONLY,SYSTEM,CURRENT_USER}[:{UNIT,SYSLOG}:IDENTIFIER]

  • Mapping of logfile settings
  • List of logfiles
root logfiles anyOf Mapping of logfile settings
